From: o-murphy <thehelixpg@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] tools/mpy_ld: support .srodata sections and absolute LO12 for RISC-V picolibc

picolibc stores floating-point constants in .srodata.cst4 / .srodata.cst8
(RISC-V small-data read-only sections).  Two issues prevented linking natmods
that use picolibc's libc.a via LINK_RUNTIME=1:

1. load_object_file only recognised sections starting with .rodata, .text,
   .bss etc.  .srodata was not on the list so those sections were skipped,
   leaving their symbols without a .section attribute and causing:

     AttributeError: 'Symbol' object has no attribute 'section'

   Fix: add ".srodata" to the accepted section-name prefixes.

2. process_riscv32_relocation handled R_RISCV_LO12_I/S with the same
   parent-lookup logic as R_RISCV_PCREL_LO12_I/S.  For the PCREL variant
   the relocation symbol is a local label pointing to the PCREL_HI20
   instruction; for the absolute variant (used by picolibc) the symbol IS
   the target data (e.g. .LC1 in .srodata.cst4), so no parent lookup is
   needed -- the address is directly s.section.addr + st_value.

   Fix: after a failed parent lookup, fall back to the direct address for
   absolute LO12; keep the assert only for PCREL_LO12 where a parent is
   always required.

Tested with gcc-riscv64-unknown-elf 14.2.0 + picolibc-riscv64-unknown-elf
1.8.10 (Ubuntu 26.04) for rv32imc and rv64imc.

Apply with: git apply mpy_ld_srodata.patch
---
 tools/mpy_ld.py | 34 ++++++++++++++++++++++++----------
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tools/mpy_ld.py b/tools/mpy_ld.py
index 02d2431c4..974a06e5f 100755
--- a/tools/mpy_ld.py
+++ b/tools/mpy_ld.py
@@ -941,21 +941,27 @@ def process_riscv32_relocation(env, text_addr, r):
         R_RISCV_LO12_S,
     ):
         parent = None
-        for potential_parent in s.section.reloc:
-            if potential_parent["r_offset"] != s["st_value"]:
-                continue
-            if potential_parent["r_info_type"] not in (
-                R_RISCV_GOT_HI20,
-                R_RISCV_PCREL_HI20,
-                R_RISCV_HI20,
-            ):
-                continue
-            parent = potential_parent
-            break
-        if parent is None:
-            assert 0, r
+        if hasattr(s.section, "reloc"):
+            for potential_parent in s.section.reloc:
+                if potential_parent["r_offset"] != s["st_value"]:
+                    continue
+                if potential_parent["r_info_type"] not in (
+                    R_RISCV_GOT_HI20,
+                    R_RISCV_PCREL_HI20,
+                    R_RISCV_HI20,
+                ):
+                    continue
+                parent = potential_parent
+                break
         addr = s.section.addr + s["st_value"]
-        reloc = parent.computed_reloc
+        if parent is not None:
+            reloc = parent.computed_reloc
+        elif r_info_type in (R_RISCV_LO12_I, R_RISCV_LO12_S):
+            # Absolute LO12: sym points directly to the data (e.g. .LC1 in
+            # .srodata.cst4 from picolibc).  The full address is already known.
+            reloc = addr + r_addend
+        else:
+            assert 0, r
         reloc_type = RISCV_RELOCATIONS_TYPE_MAP[r_info_type]

     elif r_info_type in (
@@ -1147,7 +1153,7 @@ def load_object_file(env, f, felf):
             if s.data_size == 0:
                 # Ignore empty sections
                 pass
-            elif s.name.startswith((".literal", ".text", ".rodata", ".data.rel.ro", ".bss")):
+            elif s.name.startswith((".literal", ".text", ".rodata", ".srodata", ".data.rel.ro", ".bss")):
                 sec = Section.from_elfsec(s, felf)
                 sections_shndx[idx] = sec
                 if s.name.startswith(".literal"):
